text_1:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3: 
 1.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 2.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 3.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
 4.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd:

 1.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 2.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 3.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
 4.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.

 1.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 2.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 3.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 4.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
 5.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 6.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor

 Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.

 President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.

text_1:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3: 
 1.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 2.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
 3.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 4.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.

 1.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
 2.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 3.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 4.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 5.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
 6.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.

 1.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 2.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 3.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
 4.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
 5.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 6.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor

text_1:
This happened on the day December 3rd: 
 John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 2.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 3.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 4.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 5.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 6.Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.

 2.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 3.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 4.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 5.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 6.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.

 1.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
 2.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 3.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 4.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.

 1.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 2.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
 3.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
 4.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 5.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
 6.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 2.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 3.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 4.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 5.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 6.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.

 2.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 3.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 4.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 5.Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
 6.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.

 6.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor

 Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.

text_1:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
 2.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 3.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
 4.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 5.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
 6.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.

 1.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 2.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 3.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 4.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
 5.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 6.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.

 1.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
 2.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 3.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 4.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
 5.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 6.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.

Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 2.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 3.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
 4.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
 5.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 6.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor

 1.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 2.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 3.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 4.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 5.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 6.Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.

Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.

 2.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 3.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 4.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 5.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 6.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.

 2.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 3.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 4.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 5.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 6.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
